---
import { Code } from 'astro:components';
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import CircleChart from '../components/CircleChart.astro';
import HeroMark from '../components/HeroMark.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
import ConformancePeek from '../components/ConformancePeek.astro';
import InstallCommand from '../components/InstallCommand.astro';

const heroInstall = `npm create leji`;

const peekJson = `{
  "leji": "1.0",
  "name": "your-team-context",
  "rootPath": "docs/",
  "bootProfilePath": "docs/boot-profile.md",
  "categories": {
    "domain": { "paths": ["docs/business/"] },
    "system": { "paths": ["docs/architecture/"] },
    "decisions": { "paths": ["docs/decisions/"] }
  },
  "agents": {
    "thought-partner": "docs/agents/thought-partner.md"
  },
  "owners": {
    "primary": { "name": "A. Named Owner" }
  },
  …
}`;
---

<Base>
   <div class="monument">
      <SiteHeader flush />
      <div class="wrap">
         <section class="hero">
            <div class="hero-mark reveal"><HeroMark size={150} /></div>
            <p class="inscription reveal r1">
               /LEH-jee/&ensp;·&ensp;is <em>legible</em>&ensp;·&ensp;an open specification
            </p>
            <h1 class="reveal r2">Legible to everyone<br />working in it.</h1>
            <p class="lede reveal r3">
               Leji defines the <strong>shared context layer</strong> of <a href="/ai-native/">AI-native teams</a>: one
               versioned, repo-owned record of how a team thinks (domain language, constraints, decisions, conventions,
               guardrails). People and AI agents read it on every task; changes ride the same pull-request review as
               code.
            </p>
            <div class="cta reveal r4">
               <a class="btn solid" href="/quickstart/">Start with the CLI</a>
               <a class="btn ghost" href="/spec/">Read the spec</a>
            </div>
            <div class="hero-install reveal r5">
               <InstallCommand command={heroInstall} />
            </div>
         </section>
      </div>

      <div class="wrap">
         <section class="theses">
            <article class="tablet reveal r5">
               <span class="num">I</span>
               <h2>Intent over instructions</h2>
               <p>
                  Most AI adoption writes imperative, per-vendor instructions. Leji captures durable intent (what things
                  mean, what must hold, why it is so) and lets people and agents derive actions from declared intent
                  plus task context.
               </p>
            </article>
            <article class="tablet reveal r6">
               <span class="num">II</span>
               <h2>A circle, not a tier</h2>
               <p>
                  Human-to-human, human-to-AI, and human-to-AI-to-human are first-class flows around one shared context
                  layer. Equal access, not equal authority: everyone reads, anyone proposes, people approve through pull
                  requests.
               </p>
            </article>
         </section>

         <section class="circle-diagram" aria-label="A tier compared with the circle">
            <CircleChart />
         </section>
      </div>
   </div>

   <div class="wrap">
      <section class="task-example reveal" aria-labelledby="task-example-title">
         <p class="task-eyebrow">One agent task</p>
         <h2 id="task-example-title">The same change, with a declared context layer.</h2>
         <div class="task-columns">
            <article>
               <h3>Without Leji</h3>
               <p>
                  The agent reads scattered docs, misses a decision record, repeats a stale convention, and leaves the
                  fix in chat. The code may change; the context that would prevent the next miss does not.
               </p>
            </article>
            <article>
               <h3>With Leji</h3>
               <p>
                  The agent loads <code>docs/boot-profile.md</code>, follows the mapped domain, system, and decision
                  docs, then proposes a code change and a context delta in one pull request. CI catches a stale index or
                  changelog before a person approves.
               </p>
            </article>
         </div>
      </section>
   </div>

   <div class="wrap">
      <section class="levels">
         <h2>Adopt by degrees</h2>
         <p class="levels-lede">Partial adoption is by design. Four conformance levels, each containing the last.</p>
         <ol class="ladder">
            <li>
               <code>core</code><span>manifest, boot profile, real content, a first decision, a named owner.</span>
            </li>
            <li><code>indexed</code><span>a generated index and a machine-readable changelog: a tooling run.</span></li>
            <li>
               <code>governed</code><span
                  >pull-request review for context changes, agent profiles, CI on the mechanics.</span
               >
            </li>
            <li>
               <code>federated</code><span
                  >one context layer across a multi-repo org, pinned, with sibling context layers intact.</span
               >
            </li>
         </ol>
         <ConformancePeek
            heading="See it score a layer"
            blurb="leji conformance checks each item and reports the level a context layer has actually reached. Machine-checkable items pass or fail; process items show as manual."
         />
      </section>

      <section class="manifest-peek">
         <div class="peek-text">
            <h2>One manifest file</h2>
            <p>
               <code>leji.json</code> at the repository root is the machine entrypoint: it declares the context root, the
               boot profile, the category mappings, and the conformance claim. Your existing <code>docs/</code> tree conforms
               by <em>mapping</em>, not by renaming.
            </p>
            <p>
               The cleanest context layer needs no vendor files at all: invocation points the agent host straight at the
               boot profile, zero hops. Vendor entrypoints (<code>CLAUDE.md</code>,
               <code>AGENTS.md</code>, <code>.cursor/rules</code>) are the fallback for cold starts; any you must keep
               becomes a one-line redirect, never a home.
            </p>
            <p class="peek-more"><a href="/manifest/">Manifest reference</a></p>
         </div>
         <div class="peek-code">
            <Code code={peekJson} lang="json" theme="night-owl" wrap />
         </div>
      </section>
   </div>
   <SiteFooter />
</Base>

<style>
   /* ── the monument (deep brand blue) ─────────────────── */
   .monument {
      background:
         radial-gradient(1200px 600px at 70% -10%, rgba(255, 189, 110, 0.13), transparent 60%),
         radial-gradient(900px 500px at 10% 110%, rgba(61, 86, 160, 0.5), transparent 60%), var(--blue-deep);
      color: var(--white);
      padding-bottom: 5rem;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
   }
   .monument::after {
      /* engraved fluting: faint vertical lines */
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(90deg, transparent 0 78px, rgba(255, 189, 110, 0.05) 78px 79px);
      pointer-events: none;
   }
   .monument > * {
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
   }

   .hero {
      padding: clamp(3rem, 9vh, 6.5rem) 0 4rem;
      max-width: 860px;
   }
   .hero-mark {
      margin-bottom: 1.6rem;
   }

   .inscription {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--gold-bright);
      margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
   }
   .inscription em {
      font-style: normal;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-dark);
   }

   h1 {
      font-family: var(--serif-display);
      font-size: clamp(2.7rem, 7.5vw, 5rem);
      font-weight: 480;
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 100;
      line-height: 1.04;
      letter-spacing: -0.015em;
      margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
   }

   .lede {
      font-size: clamp(1.02rem, 1.6vw, 1.18rem);
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--white-soft);
      max-width: 60ch;
      margin: 0 0 2.2rem;
   }
   .lede strong {
      color: var(--gold-bright);
      font-weight: 600;
   }

   .cta {
      display: flex;
      gap: 1rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
   }
   .btn {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      text-decoration: none;
      padding: 0.85rem 1.5rem;
      border-radius: 6px;
      transition:
         transform 0.15s ease,
         box-shadow 0.15s ease,
         background 0.15s;
   }
   .btn.solid {
      background: var(--gold);
      color: var(--blue-deep);
      font-weight: 500;
   }
   .btn.solid:hover {
      background: var(--gold-bright);
      transform: translateY(-2px);
      box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(255, 189, 110, 0.25);
   }
   .btn.ghost {
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 189, 110, 0.45);
      color: var(--gold-bright);
   }
   .btn.ghost:hover {
      border-color: var(--gold-bright);
      transform: translateY(-2px);
   }

   /* staggered reveal */
   .reveal {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(14px);
      animation: rise 0.7s cubic-bezier(0.2, 0.6, 0.2, 1) forwards;
   }
   .r1 {
      animation-delay: 0.1s;
   }
   .r2 {
      animation-delay: 0.22s;
   }
   .r3 {
      animation-delay: 0.36s;
   }
   .r4 {
      animation-delay: 0.5s;
   }
   .r5 {
      animation-delay: 0.62s;
   }
   .r6 {
      animation-delay: 0.74s;
   }
   .r7 {
      animation-delay: 0.86s;
   }
   .r8 {
      animation-delay: 0.98s;
   }

   .hero-install {
      margin-top: 1.6rem;
   }

   /* before/after task example (first light section, below the monument) */
   .task-example {
      padding: 4rem 0 0;
   }
   .task-eyebrow {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--blue);
      margin: 0 0 0.8rem;
   }
   .task-example h2 {
      font-family: var(--serif-display);
      font-weight: 560;
      font-size: 2rem;
      color: var(--blue-deep);
      margin: 0 0 1.6rem;
      max-width: 26ch;
   }
   .task-columns {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
      gap: 1.6rem 2.8rem;
   }
   .task-columns article {
      border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
      padding-left: 1.3rem;
   }
   .task-columns h3 {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--blue);
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
   }
   .task-columns p {
      color: var(--ink-soft);
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin: 0;
   }
   .task-columns code {
      font-size: 0.88em;
      color: var(--blue-deep);
      background: rgba(34, 63, 147, 0.07);
      padding: 0.1em 0.35em;
      border-radius: 4px;
   }

   @keyframes rise {
      to {
         opacity: 1;
         transform: none;
      }
   }
   @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      .reveal {
         animation: none;
         opacity: 1;
         transform: none;
      }
   }

   /* ── theses tablets ─────────────────────────────────── */
   .theses {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(290px, 1fr));
      gap: 1.4rem;
      margin-top: 0;
   }
   .tablet {
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 189, 110, 0.28);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 1.7rem 1.8rem 1.5rem;
      background: rgba(22, 41, 96, 0.45);
      /* no backdrop-filter: it forced a compositing layer Chrome sometimes
         fails to re-paint when scrolling back up, leaving blank tablets */
   }
   .tablet .num {
      font-family: var(--serif-display);
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: var(--gold);
      letter-spacing: 0.2em;
   }
   .tablet h2 {
      font-family: var(--serif-display);
      font-weight: 560;
      font-size: 1.45rem;
      margin: 0.4rem 0 0.6rem;
      color: var(--white);
   }
   .tablet p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--white-soft);
      font-size: 0.98rem;
   }

   /* circle vs tier diagram */
   .circle-diagram {
      margin-top: 2.6rem;
      border: 1px dashed rgba(255, 189, 110, 0.3);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: clamp(1rem, 3vw, 2rem);
   }

   /* ── light sections ─────────────────────────────────── */
   .levels {
      padding: 5.5rem 0 1rem;
   }
   .levels h2,
   .manifest-peek h2 {
      font-family: var(--serif-display);
      font-weight: 560;
      font-size: 2rem;
      color: var(--blue-deep);
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
   }
   .levels-lede {
      color: var(--ink-soft);
      margin-top: 0;
   }
   .ladder {
      list-style: none;
      margin: 2rem 0 0;
      padding: 0;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
      counter-reset: ladder;
   }
   .ladder li {
      counter-increment: ladder;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 1.2rem 1.3rem;
      background: var(--white);
      position: relative;
   }
   .ladder li::before {
      content: counter(ladder);
      position: absolute;
      top: -0.85rem;
      left: 1rem;
      font-family: var(--serif-display);
      font-weight: 620;
      color: var(--blue-deep);
      background: var(--gold);
      padding: 0.08rem 0.55rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      line-height: 1.45;
   }
   .ladder code {
      display: block;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--blue);
      font-weight: 500;
      margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
   }
   .ladder span {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--ink-soft);
   }

   .manifest-peek {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
      gap: 2.5rem;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 4.5rem 0 5.5rem;
   }
   .peek-text p {
      color: var(--ink-soft);
      max-width: 52ch;
   }
   .peek-more a {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--blue);
      text-decoration: none;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gold);
      padding-bottom: 2px;
   }
   .peek-more a:hover {
      color: var(--blue-soft);
      border-color: var(--gold-bright);
   }
   .peek-text code {
      background: rgba(34, 63, 147, 0.07);
      padding: 0.1em 0.35em;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 0.85em;
      color: var(--blue-deep);
   }
   .peek-code :global(.astro-code) {
      background: var(--blue-deep) !important;
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 1.4rem 1.6rem;
      font-size: var(--code-fz);
      line-height: 1.65;
      box-shadow: 0 18px 50px rgba(22, 41, 96, 0.18);
      margin: 0;
   }
</style>
